Punjab
Oct 06, 2014
Abduction, Child Sexual Abuse, Rape
Description:
			Two of the four youths involved in the alleged kidnapping and gang-raping of a 17-year-old girl were arrested here today.

The girl was allegedly kidnapped, sedated and gang-raped by four youths at Alamgir village near Ludhiana on Saturday night and later dumped near G N E College complex.

The two accused, identified as Raja and Sonu, were arrested today, Station-House-Officer Daba police station Inspector Jatinder Singh said.

One of them was living in the same colony that of the victim, he said, adding the other accused have also been identified and a search is on for them.

A manhunt had already been launched to nab the remaining two accused, the SHO said.

